
[1]delegation

   DELEGATION, n.

   1. A sending away; the act of putting in commission, or investing with
   authority to act for another; the appointment of a delegate.

   The duties of religion cannot be performed by delegation.

   2. Th persons deputed to act for another, or for others. Thus, the
   representatives of Massachusetts in Congress are called the delegation,
   or whole delegation.

   3. In the civil law, the assignment of a debt to another, as when a
   debtor appoints his debtor to answer to the creditor in his place.
